<h2><a name="line" id="line">#line</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>

Syntax:

</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#line line_number &quot;filename&quot;</span></pre>
<p>
The #line command is simply used to change the value of the <code>__LINE__</code> and
<code>__FILE__</code> variables. The filename is optional. The <code>__LINE__</code> and <code>__FILE__</code>
variables represent the current file and which line is being read. The command

</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">     <span class="co2">#line 10 &quot;main.cpp&quot;</span></pre>
<p>
…changes the current line number to 10, and the current file to “main.cpp”.
</p>

